Review written to `/data/swarm/docs/reviews/r9-rev-claude-designer.md`.

**VERDICT: APROVE WITH CHANGES** — solid foundation, no blocking defects, but two high-severity items must be resolved before freeze.

Key findings:
- **HIGH** — Body Part table lists costs but no effectiveness values (damage/harvest/heal per part), so balance can't be evaluated (§4). And Arena's "fairness + locked code" claim conflicts with server-installable Rhai mods and definable damage rules (§8/§10) — mods and world rules need to be frozen per-season too.
- **MEDIUM** — RCL downgrade wipes all progress (too punishing for persistent-world retention); progressive storage tax has an undefined 30–85% gap; fatigue system has no quantified generation/recovery; linear hit-formula risks winer-take-all; the "5-minute tutorial → write WASM" cliff is the classic churn point.
- **LOW** — lifespan vs RCL pacing mismatch, missing per-level drone caps, undefined buff/debuff stacking, placeholder spectate_delay.

Strengths called out: rock-solid determinism contract, elegant two-layer resistance system, decoupled special attacks with interrupt mechanics, the three-tier logistics switch, clean World/Arena split, AI-as-first-class-citizen via MCP, and the strong observability/debug toolchain.
